description:
In the world of Altum, a new threat has risen - a group of powerful Ascendants, naming themselves Gods. The people and creatures of Altum must decide their new allegiances, rewriting old faction lines and rivalries, and these Ascendants are not the only new concerns. Portals from another world have begun to open, and the Old Ones have begun to stir&hellip;

AutoMint is a Hero auto-battling game in a Mint Tin, inspired by Autochess, Team Fight Tactics, and other auto-battling hero games. AutoMint plays 2-4 players, and players attempt to draft and deploy the best combination of Heros to defeat their foes. The game features a modular faction system, with each faction introducing their own mechanics and powers, allowing for replayability and future expansion.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Everybody has their favorite sandwich, except for you.
Merely thinking of going to the grocery store to buy the freshest ingredients induces an existential crisis.
Luckily, there&rsquo;s a new, local sandwich shop that everyone has been raving about.  It has a daily special, and all you have to do is to add a few toppings to make the sandwich more you, even if you&rsquo;re not necessarily sure what that means.

In Oversized Sandwich, 2-4 players will play as competing indecisions within a singular indecisive person at a local sandwich shop.  In this ladder-climbing-like game, players will play cards from their hands in a way that tries to match the listed order of ingredients for the sandwich of the day.  The ingredients are putting in work as well, trying to tempt you to add them to your order with special powers that will activate either when played or once somebody completes an order.  Once a sandwich has been created with eight or more ingredients, it&rsquo;s time to check out&hellip;

But things still might not be right, so you&rsquo;ll need to try again until at least one player has been able to designate enough conviction on their favorite ingredients.  Once one player places at least five conviction markers, the game ends, and all players make sandwiches to see which version of the person they&rsquo;re playing &ldquo;wins.&rdquo;

&mdash;description from the designer

Set in the Lovecraftian universe, players are cultists, using rituals (tricks) to summon Elder Ones into the world.

After choosing the Elder One they wish to serve, they will perform rituals to call upon the Elder One. This is similar to a regular trick taking game. Here is what is different:


     Players don&rsquo;t win tricks, Elder Ones do;
     Many rituals will be conducted at the same time;
     Cards played trigger Elder Ones&rsquo; powers;
     Some rituals can stop other rituals;
     Players accumulate Madness Points for dastardly rituals;


Win condition:
The player who supports the Elder One with the most points is summoned into the world and wins. 
If two Elder Ones tie, both players win. 
Shoot the Moon: If a player supports no Elder Ones, they are considered the Investigator. If an Elder One gets no points then the Investigator is successful in stopping the cultists, and wins instead.

&mdash;description from the designer

These Lore cards have been written by the community during the Kickstarter campaign. They include a myth or legend from each country that has passed the 100 backer mark, as well as from the two countries with the most backers that haven't reached this threshold.

The Lore cards include:
- The Ankou;
- The Green Knight;
- The Sleeping Rider;
- The Dragon Slayer;
- Corriveau's Remains;
- The Bay House;
- The Pesanta;
- A Swarm of Bokkenrijders;
- The Swamp.

These cards integrate perfectly into the game if you own The Council, the Depth of Damnation expansion and/or the Sentinel and Crypt promo cards.

Requires the expansion Depth of Damnation, the cards Sentinel and Crypt and/or The Council.

The board game WHAT TO TAKE, WHAT TO LEAVE? is a simple and fun family party game that makes any gathering more exciting. It can be played with family, friends, or new acquaintances&mdash;at home, at a birthday party, with friends on a picnic, while visiting someone, or even on the go in a car, bus, train, or plane&mdash;in short, anywhere and with anyone.

&ldquo;World's richest person or immortal?&rdquo; &ldquo;Forget all your memories or lose all your dreams?&rdquo; &ldquo;Live in a new city every year or stay in the same city your whole life?&rdquo; &ldquo;Lots of money or lots of friends?&rdquo;

The game can be played in various ways, and it definitely guarantees fun and surprises. With a faster pace and answering to win, you&rsquo;ll hear unexpected answers even to simple questions. Hmm... What to take, what to leave? Should you answer truthfully, or trick others to get more cards and win the game?

For example: the player who takes a card reads out the choices on it. All players respond. Those whose answer matches the card reader's answer keep the card. Those whose answer doesn't match give the card to the reader. The player with the most cards at the end of the game wins.

If you have a more relaxed group, you can skip the competitive element and use the game as a conversation starter. Even behind seemingly simple questions and multiple-choice answers, there is usually a deep life truth or worldview.

&mdash;description from the publisher (translated)

Lauam&auml;ng MIDA V&Otilde;TTA, MIDA J&Auml;TTA? on lihtne ja l&otilde;bus kogupere seltskonnam&auml;ng, mis muudab iga koosolemise &auml;gedamaks. M&auml;ngida saab nii pere, s&otilde;prade kui ka uute tuttavatega. Kodus, s&uuml;nnip&auml;evapeol, s&otilde;pradega piknikul, k&uuml;las viibides, aga ka teel olles autos, bussis, rongis, lennukis &ndash; &uuml;hes&otilde;naga, kus ja kellega iganes.

&bdquo;Rikkaim inimene maailmas v&otilde;i surematu?&ldquo;
&bdquo;Unustad k&otilde;ik m&auml;lestused v&otilde;i kaotad k&otilde;ik unistused?&ldquo;
&bdquo;Elad iga aasta uues linnas v&otilde;i kogu elu samas linnas?&ldquo;
