MIDA V&Otilde;TTA, MIDA J&Auml;TTA? m&auml;ngu saab m&auml;ngida mitmel viisil ning nalja ja &uuml;llatusi saab kindlasti. Suurema tempoga ja v&otilde;idu vastates kuuleb ka lihtsatele k&uuml;simustele ootamatuid vastuseid. Hmm... Mida v&otilde;tta, mida j&auml;tta? Kas vastata nii, nagu p&auml;riselt m&otilde;tled, v&otilde;i trikitada, et saada endale rohkem kaarte ning v&otilde;ita m&auml;ng?

N&auml;iteks nii: m&auml;ngija, kes v&otilde;tab kaardi, loeb ette sellel olevad valikud. Vastavad k&otilde;ik m&auml;ngijad. Need, kelle vastus klapib kaardi ettelugeja vastusega, j&auml;tavad kaardi endale. Need, kelle vastus ei klapi, loovutavad kaardi sellele, kes luges k&uuml;simuse. V&otilde;idab see, kellel on m&auml;ngu l&otilde;puks k&otilde;ige rohkem kaarte.

Kui koos on rahulikum seltskond, siis j&auml;tke v&otilde;istluselement v&auml;lja ja kasutage m&auml;ngu vestluskaartidena. Ka pealtn&auml;ha v&auml;ga lihtsa k&uuml;simuse ja valikvastuste taga on reeglina peidus s&uuml;gav elut&otilde;de ning maailmavaade.

&mdash;description from the publisher

It&rsquo;s time to roll the dice! Friends of the card game Gigi Gacker will flock to the dice-pecker-worm buffet&thinsp;&hellip; and all young hens who love wormy appetisers.

Just 3 dice per player are enough to create a big cackle on the chicken menu board. At the start of each game round, a worm snack is laid out on the buffet for each player&thinsp;&ndash;&thinsp;in different sizes and flavours. According to the familiar Gigi Gacker game principle, the biggest&thinsp;&ndash;&thinsp;and now &lsquo;strongest&rsquo;&thinsp;&ndash;&thinsp;chicken always grabs the first morsel on the buffet&thinsp;&ndash;&thinsp;even if it is not the tastiest. In the dice rounds, all the &lsquo;tactical&nbsp;tricks&rsquo; are used to fight for the biggest morsels. Less tasty worms themselves can be used as &lsquo;dice substitutes&rsquo; or simply &lsquo;added&rsquo; to the neighbouring plates. It is also very popular to reverse the order of the courses on the buffet until the competition is at the very back. Apart from that, some starters are extremely inedible and carry minus points&thinsp;&hellip;

&mdash;description from the publisher
